Personal Assistant to the President on New Media, Bashir Ahmed, has debunked social media reports that President Muhammadu Buhari has embarked on 20-day vacation to London on Saturday. NAN reports that some online media outfits, had on Saturday reported that the president departed Abuja on April 9, 2022, for another three weeks vacation in London. However, Ahmed via his twitter account on Saturday said, “The news going round that President Muhammadu Buhari has embarked on a 20-day vacation trip to London is fake. ”The president is in Abuja and he is not planning to embark on any trip to London.”